The paper focuses on the development of a structured methodology for the construction of spreadsheet models, which is a software engineering process. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the improvement of the methodology, which involves programming language concepts and techniques, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a likely sub-category as well. The objective of the methodology is to reduce user-generated errors, which relates to human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another possible sub-category. The experiments conducted to evaluate the methodology involve real-life data, which suggests that cs.DB (Databases) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential benefits of the methodology, which could be relevant to the broader field of cybernetics, making cs.CY (Cybernetics) a possible sub-category.
